title: Great sandwiches to go and pastries
text: Great variety of fresh sandwiches for picnics and grab n go. Pastries were delicious and fresh. Perfect spot to hit before exploring the city.

title: Cute cafe, expected more
text: Nice neighborhood cafe. Grabbed some pizza to go for the kids. Was disappointed based upon the prior reviews. ‘Armstrong’ pizza was billed as sausage and meat. Looked like a hot dog was sliced on top and a few pieces of bacon. Much better choices around.

title: What you’d expect right off the Ramblas
text: First night in town and getting my bearings. Food was decent but didn’t compare to the restaurants in the neighborhoods like Gracia and off the main strip. Better as a bar than a restaurant. What do you expect right off the touristy drag? Over priced.

title: Quick Tapas - Friendly Service
text: Popped in for a few tapas before a dinner at a neighboring restaurant. Nice tapas menu, friendly smiles, tasty food. It was packed and obviously a neighborhood favorite. Would recommend and hope to return on a future trip for dinner.

title: Fantastic cozy restaurant
text: Great meal and great service. Would recommend and go again. Steak and tuna and angry potatoes were a hit.

title: Solid Italian dinner
text: Nice meal. Attentive service. Good pasta and wine choices. The risotto, lasagna and gnocchi were all good.

title: Delicious!
text: Hit this awesome gelato place twice while staying in Gracia. Fabulous little spot with great hazelnut and chocolate gelato. Yum!

title: Our best meal in Spain... Hands down.
text: Although we didn’t have a reservation, we lucked out on some other cancellation and got a table. Everything was amazing. Specials were mouth watering- venison, rice with chicken shrimp, duck with morels. Appetizers were killer, and the service was the best of all the restaurants we visited. Can’t recommend highly enough.

title: Simply amazing.
text: Another killer meal of amazing seafood tapas. The honey encrusted Cod, seafood salad, tenderloin bruschetta, and monkfish were all to die for. Very busy but worth sitting at the counter if the wait for a table is too long. And don’t skip the bread pudding.
